# Applied-Ai-ASSIGNMENT-1

## Assignment 1 — K-Means Clustering
"You are a data analyst at a retail company. Given a dataset of customer purchase history
(annual income, spending score, age), implement K-Means clustering from scratch using Python.
Determine the optimal number of clusters using the Elbow Method and Silhouette Score.
Visualise the clusters using a 2D scatter plot and interpret which customer segment is most
valuable to the business."
What to implement: KMeans from sklearn.cluster, silhouette_score, matplotlib scatter plots,
Elbow curve plotting.
## Assignment 2 — DBSCAN for Anomaly Detection
"A cybersecurity firm has collected network traffic logs with features such as packet size,
connection duration, and request frequency. Using DBSCAN, identify anomalous (noisy) data
points that could represent potential intrusions. Compare DBSCAN's cluster results with K-Means
on the same dataset and explain why DBSCAN is better suited for this task."
What to implement: DBSCAN from sklearn.cluster, eps and min_samples tuning, noise point
extraction, side-by-side comparison plot.

## Assignment 3 — PCA for Dimensionality Reduction
"You are given the MNIST handwritten digit dataset (784 features per image). Apply PCA to
reduce the dimensions to 2D and 50D. Plot the 2D projection coloured by digit class. Compute
the cumulative explained variance and determine the minimum number of components needed
to retain 95% of variance. Discuss the trade-off between information loss and computational
efficiency."
What to implement: PCA from sklearn.decomposition, explained_variance_ratio_, cumulative
variance plot, matplotlib 2D scatter.

## Assignment 4 — K-Means + PCA pipeline
"Using the Iris dataset, first apply PCA to reduce features to 2 components, then apply K-Means
clustering on the reduced data. Evaluate cluster purity against the true labels using the Adjusted
Rand Index. Compare clustering performance before and after PCA. Visualise both pipelines side
by side."
What to implement: Pipeline from sklearn, adjusted_rand_score, before/after comparison.

## Assignment 5 — Logistic Regression
"A hospital wants to predict whether a patient has diabetes based on diagnostic measurements
(Pima Indians Diabetes Dataset). Implement Logistic Regression with and without regularisation

(L1, L2). Plot the ROC curve and compute AUC. Tune the regularisation parameter C using cross-
validation and report precision, recall, and F1-score."

What to implement: LogisticRegression with penalty, roc_curve, cross_val_score,
classification_report.

## Assignment 6 — Support Vector Machine (SVM)
"You are given a binary classification problem on the Breast Cancer Wisconsin dataset. Train an
SVM classifier using linear, polynomial, and RBF kernels. Plot the decision boundary for a 2-
feature subset using PCA. Perform hyperparameter tuning on C and gamma using GridSearchCV
and report the best configuration."
What to implement: SVC from sklearn.svm, kernel comparison, GridSearchCV, decision
boundary visualisation with mlxtend or manual mesh.

## Assignment 7 — Random Forest Classifier
"A financial institution wants to predict loan default risk. Using the LendingClub or a synthetic
loan dataset, train a Random Forest model. Extract and plot feature importances. Compare
performance at different n_estimators values. Implement Out-of-Bag (OOB) error estimation
and plot learning curves."
What to implement: RandomForestClassifier, feature_importances_, oob_score=True,
learning_curve from sklearn.

## Assignment 8 — Model Comparison: LR vs SVM vs Random Forest
"Using the Heart Disease UCI dataset, train and evaluate Logistic Regression, SVM (RBF kernel),

and Random Forest classifiers. For each model, report accuracy, precision, recall, F1, and AUC-
ROC. Plot all three ROC curves on a single graph. Perform 5-fold stratified cross-validation.

Present a final recommendation table."
